<H2>1. Features</H2>
<ul>
    <li>Connects to a local SQLite3 database using Spring JDBC</li>
    <li>Reads a provided Excel template (.xlsx) using Apache POI</li>
    <li>Injects rows into a specified worksheet using data from the database</li>
    <li>Exports the result to a new Excel file</li>
    <li>Configuration via <code>application.yml</code></li>
</ul>


<H2>2. Project Structure</H2>
<p>
    The application uses Kotlin + Spring Boot 3 and is organized into components for JDBC access,
    Excel processing (via Apache POI), configuration, and CLI-style execution.
</p>

<CodeBlockSyntax Language="plaintext" EnableLineNumbers="false" EnableCopyButton="true"><pre>
org.cameek.spring_excel/
├── cli/
│   └── ExcelRunner.kt       # ApplicationRunner that loads template & writes Excel output
├── db/
│   └── DataInitializer.kt   # Populates SQLite with test metric data
├── resources/
│   └── template.xlsx        # Excel template (formatted, can contain charts)
│   └── application.yml      # Configuration for Sqlite3, paths and date ranges
└── SpringExcelApplication.kt
</pre></CodeBlockSyntax>


