<H2>4. App Config Example in application.yml</H2>

<ul>
    <li>Configuration for SQLite3 JDBC driver, path to local DB, optionally username and password</li>
    <li>Source Excel template path</li>
    <li>Output Excel file path</li>
    <li>SQL query date range</li>
</ul>

<CodeBlockSyntax Language="yaml" EnableLineNumbers="true" EnableCopyButton="true"><pre>
spring:
  application:
    name: org.cameek.spring_excel
  datasource:
    driver-class-name: org.sqlite.JDBC
    url: jdbc:sqlite:metrics.db
    username: 
    password: 
    
excel:
  template: src/main/resources/template.xlsx
  output: report-output.xlsx

report:
  start-date: '2025-01-01'
  end-date: '2025-12-31'
</pre></CodeBlockSyntax>


<H2>5. Fake Data for SQLite</H2>
<p>
    On startup, the app creates a simple <code>metrics</code> table and inserts 30 days of test data:
</p>

<CodeBlockSyntax Language="kotlin" EnableLineNumbers="true" EnableCopyButton="true"><pre>
package org.cameek.spring_excel.db

import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct
import org.springframework.jdbc.core.JdbcTemplate
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component
import java.time.LocalDate
import kotlin.random.Random

@@Component
class DataInitializer(private val jdbcTemplate: JdbcTemplate) {

    @@PostConstruct
    fun initialize() {
        jdbcTemplate.execute("CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS metrics(date TEXT, metric REAL)")

        jdbcTemplate.execute("DELETE FROM metrics")

        val now = LocalDate.now()
        for (i in 0..29) {
            jdbcTemplate.update(
                "INSERT INTO metrics(date, metric) VALUES (?,?)",
                now.minusDays(i.toLong()).toString(),
                Random.nextDouble(0.0, 100.0)
            )
        }
    }
}

</pre></CodeBlockSyntax>


